  "prompt": "Do people working at IMEC get a holiday during good friday?",
  "response": "Yes, employees at IMEC, like many other organizations in countries where Good Friday is a recognized public holiday, typically get the day off. Good Friday is a Christian holiday observed on the Friday before Easter Sunday, commemorating the crucifixion of Jesus Christ.\n\nWhether IMEC employees receive Good Friday as a holiday depends on the company's policies and the local laws of the country where the IMEC office is located. For instance, in Belgium, where IMEC's headquarters are based, Good Friday is not an official public holiday, but some organizations, especially those with international or Christian traditions, may grant employees the day off or allow them to take it as a personal day. It's best to check IMEC's specific holiday policy or consult with HR for confirmation.",
